tsJKBovHW8yXvIXzfIic_aU6Q3g==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test configuration issues**\\n\\nI’m noticing that there might be no config. It seems like tck handles could help here. The user filter only includes a library for coverage, but the agent might capture everything. Existing native test results passed, which is good. However, for the nested test task, there's a chance no metadata was generated after test compilation. I think I also need to think about package naming. I'll create that next.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_6aO5xgcYCr5rUWOoEQdsaSVw|fc_0fce880121b8d1d4016a26e4404bd88193ad2896754c8a12e6", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.wiremock/wiremock/3.13.1/src/test/java/org_wiremock/wiremock/AdminRoutesInnerRouteBuilderTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_wiremock.wiremock;\n\nimport static com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.http.RequestMethod.GET;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.admin.AdminRoutes;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.admin.AdminTask;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.admin.RequestSpec;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.admin.Router;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.common.url.PathParams;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.core.Admin;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.extension.AdminApiExtension;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.http.ResponseDefinition;\nimport com.github.tomakehurst.wiremock.stubbing.ServeEvent;\nimport java.util.List;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\npublic class AdminRoutesInnerRouteBuilderTest {\n    @Test\n    void adminApiExtensionRegistersTaskFromTaskClass() {\n        AdminRoutes routes = AdminRoutes.forServer(List.of(new ClassBasedRouteExtension()), null);\n\n        AdminTask adminTask = routes.taskFor(GET, \"/extension/class-based-route\");\n        RequestSpec requestSpec = routes.requestSpecForTask(ClassBasedRouteTask.class);\n\n        assertThat(adminTask).isInstanceOf(ClassBasedRouteTask.class);\n        assertThat(requestSpec.method()).isEqualTo(GET);\n        assertThat(requestSpec.path()).isEqualTo(\"/extension/class-based-route\");\n    }\n\n    public static class ClassBasedRouteExtension implements AdminApiExtension {\n        @Override\n        public String getName() {\n            return \"class-based-route-extension\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public void contributeAdminApiRoutes(Router router) {\n            router.add(GET, \"/extension/class-based-route\", ClassBasedRouteTask.class);\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ClassBasedRouteTask implements AdminTask {\n        @Override\n        public ResponseDefinition execute(Admin admin, ServeEvent serveEvent, PathParams pathParams) {\n            return new ResponseDefinition(200, \"class-based-route\");\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 688, "output": 635, "cacheRead": 23040, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 24363, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780933691216, "responseId": "resp_0fce880121b8d1d4016a26e43bcff08193b993f7d595dcc802"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_6aO5xgcYCr5rUWOoEQdsaSVw|fc_0fce880121b8d1d4016a26e4404bd88193ad2896754c8a12e6", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 2210 bytes to tests/src/org.wiremock/wiremock/3.13.1/src/test/java/org_wiremock/wiremock/AdminRoutesInnerRouteBuilderTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1780933701308}]}
